parameters:
Thief Nora: ...I can faintly smell blood. There might be
something happening inside.
Clea: Understood, let's prepare to fight and go inside.
Shall we enter the fisherman's hut?

Cors the Wanderer: That fisherman's hut from earlier is
actually a brothel used by people of high status.

Cors the Wanderer: That corpse was also a fairly wealthy
noble... Similar incidents have been occurring frequently in
the vicinity of Mucos.
Cors the Wanderer: By the way, did you see the corpse?

Clea: It seems like their throat was slashed with a sharp
blade.

Cors the Wanderer: It's strange that the method of killing
is always the same, whether it's nobles or merchants, anyone
can be killed.

Cors the Wanderer: Because of that, Mucos is on the verge of
exploding.
Clea: Do you have any leads on the culprit?

Cors the Wanderer: I have no idea... There are various
theories, but I suspect it's the same culprit.

Cors the Wanderer: There's an organization that simply kills
without taking any valuables, they're called the 'Dagger of
Deirei' as a nickname.
Cors the Wanderer: By the way, why are you here?
Thief Nora: I'll explain it to you!

Cors the Wanderer: So they're targeting beastmen nobles...
I'm not familiar with the Oros region, so I can't say for
sure.

Cors the Wanderer: The most likely possibility would be the
golden city of Dromos. There are many vulgar people there
who let money speak for them.

Cors the Wanderer: For the time being, I plan to investigate
at the fishing grounds. If anything happens, please come
here and I should be able to meet you easily.

Cors the Wanderer: Well then, I'll take care of disposing of
the bodies and compensating my subordinates around here.

Thief Nora: Our tools are sharp blades, and our targets are
only the wealthy.
Thief Nora: The culprit... it's not the captain, right?
Clea: Wouldn't Nora-san understand that the most?

Priestess Sophia: He must have sworn to never betray Nora-
chan since the disbandment of the Emma Thief Guild.

Mage Relm: He's the one who was investigating Oros! He
wouldn't commit crimes in Mucos for no reason!
Thief Nora: That's right, thank you very much!

Thief Nora: I also absolutely absolutely believe in the
captain!

Clea: We didn't get any useful information. Let's wait for a
message from Clevo-san.

Male Sailor: Since we've finally come ashore, let's buy a
woman and have some fun.

Male Fisherman: This is a fishing spot. If you want to go
swimming, go to Lepton!
